BergInnkeeper			~kBastiane d'Ile, face flushed, says to you, "Come, sit down and drink before your mouth dries up!  I also make it a little warmer in here, so you won't freeze."
BergInnkeeper			~kBastiane d'Ile laughs, "Believe me, I miss all the luxuries our family once had.  If I didn't have to work, <hick> I wouldn't!  Damn it!"
BergInnkeeper			~kBastiane d'Ile stammers drunkenly, "W-What do you think, who stands before you, huh?!  I don't really belong here.  After all, I was once Bastiane d'Ile!"
BergVaultman			~kLiam Magnus says, "This Harold fellow and his son hold quite a bit 'v sway over our king and I'm not sure that's in Berg's best interest.  But let's talk business:  What is it ye want to deposit?"
BergVaultman			~kLiam Magnus is caught in a violent coughing fit as smoke billows from the chimney. Leaning heavily on his cane, he mutters a few inaudible curses.
BergVaultman			~kLiam Magnus says, "Well met!  Are ye visitin' from tha Western Kingdom?  I've been told that ye Westerners've got a similar vault in the royal city 'v Barloque?  It's probably nowhere near as big and professionally maintained as mine, don't ye agree?  Anyway, would ye like ta keep a few things here?"
BergVaultman			~kLiam Magnus says, "Are ye familiar with the auction house around here?  Well, I'm sure it'd be runnin' more smoothly if I were responsible fer it, but I guess our king has his reasons fer trustin' the current manager...  Oh well, back to business:  Leave yer valuables with me and I'll keep'em safe fer ye fer a small fee.  How about it?"
BergVaultman			~kLiam Magnus adds more firewood to the chimney, keeping his vault nice and toasty.
